20596.「また 会いましたね <cs_pchero>さん。\n バトリンピック・予選のチ:
We meet again, <cs_pchero>.
This is the checkpoint for the Battlympics
Qualifiers.

20597.「お忘れですか？\n 前に 月光の花を集めていただいた者ですよ。\n その節は:
Do you remember? I had asked you before to
collect Moonlight Flowers for me. Thank you
again for helping me with that.

20598.「今は こちらで 予選の係員を務めていますよ。\n <cs_pchero>さんと:
I'm now an official for the qualifiers. I was
hoping that I would run into you here.

20599.「あなたなら きっと 決勝バトルを勝ち抜き\n 優勝することも 夢ではないんでし:
For you, I'm sure that winning the final
battle and becoming champion is not just
a dream.

20600.「まあ それも 予選を突破すればの話……:
That is...if you can make it through the
qualifiers...

20601.「残念ながら あなたが 闘士の割符を手に\n 戻ることはないでしょう。:
Unfortunately for you, you will not be
returning with a Fighters' Tally.

20602.「……あなたは 余計なことを知ってしまった。\n そんな あなたに 生きていても:
You know too much...and there are people that
see your being alive as a problem.

20603.「先ほどは まんまと 逃げられましたが\n やはり ここで待っていれば 現れまし:
You did manage to escape, but I knew you'd
show up again if I waited for you here.
How very dutiful of you!

20604.「今度こそ 逃がしませんよ。\n 我が主のために 死んでもらいます！:
But there will be no running this time.
You must die for the sake of my master!

20605.「どうやら 手助けの必要は なかったようだな。: Guess you didn't need my help this time.

20606.「ああ。こいつ 逃げようとしてたんで\n ちょいとばかし なでといたぜ。:
Yep. This guy was trying to make a run for it,
so I gave him a pat on the ol' noggin.

20607.「しかし アンタが 参加してるのを狙って\n こいつが 係員をやってたんなら\n:
But if he was working as an official just to
try and target you, this tournament doesn't
seem so legit after all...

20608.「さて それじゃ オレは失礼する！\n ……この男のことは まかせてもらうぜ。\:
Alright, then, I'm off! Don't worry, I'll
take care of this guy. I'm the one who
caught him, after all.

20609.「アンタも 聞きたいこととかあるだろうが\n オレのほうの用件を 優先させてもら:
I'm sure you have tons of questions you want
to ask me, but my business comes first...
Oh, and don't forget this!

31994.「……確かに これは 闘士の割符。\n これで <pc>選手の予選は\n 終了と:
Yep, this is a Fighters' Tally all right.
And with that, you're all good and
qualified.

31995.「そして 同時に 第１回バトリンピックの\n 予選全体も 終了とさせていただきま:
And so, the first round of the Battlympics
is officially concluded! You were
actually the last contestant to finish!

31997.「おめでとうございます！！\n あなたは バトリンピック決勝バトル\n ４人目の:
Congratulations!!
You've made it to the finals of the
Battlympics as the fourth contestant!

31998.「ほう。<pc>は 残ったのか。\n まずは おめでとうと言わせてもらおう。:
Huh... So you made it, huh?
First of all, let me congratulate you.

31999.「これは セインズ選手。\n もしかして 予選結果を聞きにこられたので？:
This is Sainz. Perhaps you came here to know
the results of the qualifiers?

32000.「どうしても 落ち着かなくってな……。\n そろそろ 全参加者の予選が終わって\:
I was feeling a bit anxious... I figured by
now that all of the participants would've
qualified, right?

32001.「ンフフフ……。\n 何を 心配することが ありましょう？\n セインズ選手は:
Hmm hmm hmm... What's the worry?
You're the clear winner, you know.

32002.「わずか ４名だけの 決勝進出者の中に\n 同じ ジェイコフ氏の弟子が ふたりも:
I was surprised to see that out of only four
finalists, two of them were pupils under
Jakov.

32003.「オレは 元弟子だけどな。\n ……っと ウワサをすれば なんとやらだ。:
...Former pupil.
Oh, and speak of the devil...

32005.「……んで どうだった <pc>？\n 予選は 無事 突破できたのか？:
...Well? How'd it go, <pc>?
Did you manage to qualify?

32006.「ンフフフ……。\n <pc>選手も セインズ選手も\n 見事 予選を突破なさい:
Hmm hmm hmm... Both <pc> and
Sainz here made it through the qualifiers.

32007.「セインズも 参加してんのかよ……。\n まあ とにかく 修行は達成できたわけだ:
So you're in on it too, eh Sainz...
Well, anyways...with that, you've finished
your training. Here, take this.

32008.「ところで 予選の順位は どうだったんだ？\n セインズと <pc>の\n どっ:
By the way, how high did you rank in the
qualifiers? Did you beat Sainz?

32009.「ンフフフ……。\n セインズ選手が 予選１位通過。\n <pc>選手が 予選４:
Hmm hmm hmm...
Sainz qualified in 1st place, and
<pc> qualified in 4th.

32011.「クッ…… いい気になるなよ セインズ！\n 決勝では 必ず <pc>が テメー:
Ngh... Don't get cocky, you hear?! I'll make
sure <pc> wipes that smug look off
your face in the finals!!

32012.「まあ 予選なんて しょせん お遊び。\n バトルマスターの実力とは 関係ないか:
Well, qualifiers are just for fun and don't
really show off our skills anyway. After
all, battlemasters need to fight, right?

32013.「もちろん 決勝バトルで 当たっても\n 後輩相手に 負けるつもりなんて\n こ:
Of course, I have no intention of losing to
someone my junior in the finals!

32014.「……そういうワケだ <pc>。\n 決勝で戦えるのを 楽しみにしてるぜ。\n:
So that's why I'm looking forward to seeing
you in the finals. Don't let me down!

32015.「ンフフフ……。じつに すばらしいっ！\n 同じ師を持つ ふたりのバトルマスター:
Hmm hmm hmm... How amazing!
Sparks flying between two battlemasters under
the same master! Things are getting heated!

32016.「バトリンピック・決勝バトル……\n これは がぜん 盛り上がってまいりましたよ:
The final battle of the Battlympics...
It's getting even more exciting! Hmm hmm
hmm...
